Penz 2007
), one pair of apical tibial spurs present on mid and hind legs. Wing shape uniform between males and females; forewing triangular-shaped, distal margin straight or only slightly concave; hind wing oval-shaped, margins slightly scalloped. Dorsally, wings orange (
batea , catharinae
) or yellow (
bassus
